sys_hub_flow.copied_from_name: Send a Document for Digital Sign
sys_hub_flow.description:
The flow shows an implementation of Docusign actions for sending a document for digital Signature. The flow is triggered based on a Catalog Item.

Trigger: The flow is triggered every time a Service Catalog request is created and the catalog request item is 'Send a Document for Digital Signature'.

Flow Steps:

  1. Get Catalog Variables: The step retrieves the catalog variables from the Request Item using Get Catalog variables action.
  2. Lookup Attachment Record: The step retrieves the attachment record of the document attached to Catalog Item.
  3. Send Adhoc Signature Request to User: The step sends the document to the recipient for Signing.
  4. The state of the Request Item is changed based on the state of the Envelope record being Completed, Declined or Voided.
  5. Error is logged in case of errors when Sending the Document for Signature.

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.

sys_hub_flow_snapshot.description:
The flow shows an implementation of Docusign actions for sending a document for digital Signature. The flow is triggered based on a Catalog Item.

Trigger: The flow is triggered every time a Service Catalog request is created and the catalog request item is 'Send a Document for Digital Signature'.

Flow Steps:

  1. Get Catalog Variables: The step retrieves the catalog variables from the Request Item using Get Catalog variables action.
  2. Lookup Attachment Record: The step retrieves the attachment record of the document attached to Catalog Item.
  3. Send Adhoc Signature Request to User: The step sends the document to the recipient for Signing.
  4. The state of the Request Item is changed based on the state of the Envelope record being Completed, Declined or Voided.
  5. Error is logged in case of errors when Sending the Document for Signature.

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
